    <item>
      <title>Goal Smashed! - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Sep 2025 02:07:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13596" class="post-13596 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Goal Smashed!&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Last night, I ended August with a 90-minute bug hunt during the fireworks. It may sound like a long time, but it went by so quickly! I was even a bit surprised when the clock struck midnight, and everything abruptly ended.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="That's it for the Fireworks Show!" class="wp-image-13597" sizes="(max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The fireworks stopped, the festive music switched back to the normal sleepy tunes, and the bugs turned into pumpkins. Well, not pumpkins, but they basically turned into worthless crickets. 😆 That wrapped up my favorite time of year in Animal Crossing, and it&amp;#8217;s kinda sad when it all ends in the blink of an eye.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Outside of town hall, Tortimer was still standing there, but now without a purpose. He said he&amp;#8217;s too excited to sleep after fireworks shows.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="Tortimer: I'm always too excited to sleep after the Fireworks Show..." class="wp-image-13598" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I made about 310k in my final bug hunt of the year, and that brings me to the main topic of the day&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;My Summer Goal&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Just to recap, I made a summer bell goal at the &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/"&gt;end of June&lt;/a&gt;. At the time, I had 67,650,000 bells in the bank. My goal was to earn 2.35 million more bells over the summer, so that my total balance would reach 70 million bells by September 1st.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Throughout July, I averaged about three bug hunts a week, generally playing at least an hour and often more. I reached my goal of 70 million bells saved&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="Your current balance is 70,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-13599" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8230;on July 27th. I still had over a month to go though, so I set a new goal for myself (even though I didn&amp;#8217;t post it publicly): 72 million bells. That&amp;#8217;s roughly double my original goal. By August 13th, I had met that goal as well. 🎯&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;#8217;t make any additional goals, and my bug hunt time slowed down (slightly) for the 2nd half of August. But I still kept playing at least twice a week. When I started up the game today, my balance sat at 73,630,000 bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="Your current balance is 73,630,000 bells." class="wp-image-13600" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So I made nearly six million bells in that two month span, which I&amp;#8217;m pretty sure is my personal best. That&amp;#8217;s more than 2.5 times my original target. My long-term goal of 100 million bells (to earn the green feather) is actually starting to look achievable in the next few years if I keep this up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Of course, there&amp;#8217;s no guarantee that I&amp;#8217;ll be able to do this every summer. If we get a new Animal Crossing game soon, I probably won&amp;#8217;t be playing City Folk as much, for example. But that green feather no longer seems decades away. 🪶&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;Labor Day&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In other news, today is Labor Day in the U.S., so Tortimer was standing outside of town hall once again.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="Tortimer: Today is Labor Day, sprout." class="wp-image-13602" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a picnic basket for the occasion. When I spoke to him several more times, he eventually gave me a surprisingly encouraging pep talk.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="Tortimer: Sometimes your hard work may go unnoticed, but never forget this, sprout: I'm rooting for you, 100%!" class="wp-image-13604" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Up by Nookington&amp;#8217;s, Felicity was talking about Tom Nook&amp;#8217;s popularity. She said even the people in the city have heard of him, and she wondered if it was true that he had a shop in the city a long time ago.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="Felicity: I wonder if it's really true that he had a shop in the city a long time ago? Hmmmm..." class="wp-image-13603" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Some of this stuff goes back to Wild World, but it&amp;#8217;s nice to see it referenced in City Folk as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ve had two recent bug requests: Nana has been looking for a darner dragonfly, and Biskit has been seeking a longhorn beetle. Unfortunately, both of them are only out in the daytime, and I&amp;#8217;ve been mostly playing at night lately. I did play in the day today, but it was raining, which kept away the dragonflies. And the longhorn beetle seems to be pretty rare, and only appears on stumps. I didn&amp;#8217;t find either bug, so Nana and Biskit are both going to be disappointed in me.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I ran into Felicity again by the museum, and she was grossed out by the rain. She even compared herself to a swamp with legs. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/Array" alt="Felicity: OHMIGOSH, dumbbell! I just feel all wet and sticky and GROSS! I'm like a swamp with legs." class="wp-image-13605" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Did you all have a good summer? Did you do lots of bug hunting and make lots of bells? Let me know in the comments!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time. Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/01/goal-smashed/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-01T22:07:21-04:00"&gt;September 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-01T22:32:10-04:00"&gt;September 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/accf-fw-done.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Farmer&amp;#039;s Letter - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Sep 2025 01:02:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-6008" class="post-6008 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;The Farmer&amp;#8217;s Letter&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;It was storming when I played the game on Thursday afternoon. I promptly checked my mail and found a goodbye letter from Coco! I&amp;#8217;m sad to see her go, but I can&amp;#8217;t say I&amp;#8217;m surprised.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Jeff, FYI: I recently decided to move for reasons I prefer not to go into. I can't tell you where I'm going, but I wills ay this: I won't forget you! Best of luck--to both of us! Goodbye! -Coco" class="wp-image-6009" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, I was certainly happy with her replacement: Mitzi the cute cat! She moved in next door to Maple, in the spot where Hank originally lived, many years ago.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Mitzi: So...are you new in town? How splendid! Would you... Uh... Would you like to be friends with me?" class="wp-image-6010" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mitzi last lived in Forest back in 2014. Welcome back, Mitzi! 😊&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I spoke with Static, he called me completely bonkers for not buying Saharah&amp;#8217;s carpets&amp;#8230;even though I never said such a thing. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Static: Are you completely bonkers?! Saharah's carpets are exotic and just insanely rare! You can't buy them at the store." class="wp-image-6011" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Over by the wishing well, Ursala told me she doesn&amp;#8217;t normally mind the rain unless it sticks around too long.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Ursala: I don't mind the rain, but it gets really annoying when it sticks around for too long." class="wp-image-6012" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And then she said it&amp;#8217;s the same situation with me. Thanks a lot, Ursala.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Ursala: Jeff, the rain is a lot like you, actually, grooomph." class="wp-image-6013" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I really like Emerald&amp;#8217;s umbrella; it looks like a giant flower walking around when she&amp;#8217;s facing away from the camera. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="A giant flower...or is just Emerald holding an umbrella?" class="wp-image-6014" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Behind Candi&amp;#8217;s house, I spotted this huge fish shadow!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Trying to fish out a huge shadow." class="wp-image-6015" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Or at least, that&amp;#8217;s what I thought. But it turned out to just be an old tire. Oof. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Friday, Belle threatened to &amp;#8220;whale into me.&amp;#8221; All I did was talk to her, so I have no clue what she was mad about this time. 🤷&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Belle: Hey, watch it, Speedy! If I didn't have like, lightning-quick reflexes, I would've whaled into you!" class="wp-image-6019" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A bit later, I had a little argument with Candi. Since it happened on a bridge, and I just happened to be holding a net, I took advantage of the glitch that lets me push her into the river. It wasn&amp;#8217;t planned or anything, honest! But now she&amp;#8217;s in over her head. 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Candi, in the river: You can just forget about being friends with me, sweetie!" class="wp-image-6020" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Baabara asked me for a walker cicada that I had caught moments earlier. She wanted it for her niece, and she offered me a staggering 2,680 bells for it! It&amp;#8217;s not even a rare bug! I gladly agreed to the sale.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Baabara: Really? Why, thanks! I know I may seem aloof, but I'm a sucker for my niece... Here's your 2,680 bells." class="wp-image-6021" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I can&amp;#8217;t imagine why Baabara was being so nice for a change. Maybe it was a glitch in the game too. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was a camper&amp;#8217;s tent in town, and Sprocket the mechanical ostrich was inside. He wanted to play a game with me, but he would get all the money in my pockets if I lost. I had over 47,000 bells on me, so I was not about to risk that much!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Sprocket, at the campsite: But if you're wrong, then I get all the money you have on you!" class="wp-image-6022" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I played again today (August 31st), and the last day of every month is raffle day. Even though I didn&amp;#8217;t have any raffle tickets, I still like to go in and take a look at the prizes. An Arwing (the ship from Star Fox) was one of them. Pretty cool.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="347" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Tom Nook: ...Oh no! How unfortunate! You don't have five raffle tickets with you!" class="wp-image-6023" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rocco wanted to sell me a botanical shirt for 2,060 bells. He said it was too fancy for him, but he thought I&amp;#8217;d like it because I&amp;#8217;m a &amp;#8220;trendy little wannabe.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="347" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Rocco: It's too fancy-pants for me. You're sort of a trendy little wannabe, though, so it's probably right up your alley." class="wp-image-6024" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But I had no interest in paying 2k for a shirt! I declined the offer, and Rocco said he&amp;#8217;d just take it over to Tom Nook&amp;#8217;s store and sell it. Go ahead and try! Tom Nook isn&amp;#8217;t buying anything today, and he would never pay anywhere near that amount for a shirt anyway!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Emerald showed me a weird letter she got in the mail, supposedly from a farmer who planted flowers all around Forest. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="347" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/Array" alt="Tell me, Emerald... When I first came, there was nothing. The emptiness saddened me, and I bent my will to planting flowers. Is this village not better for my efforts? -From Farmer" class="wp-image-6025" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That&amp;#8217;s pretty interesting, and I really like the farmer&amp;#8217;s choice of stationery too. Very fitting&amp;#8230;but I wonder why the farmer didn&amp;#8217;t stick around and put down some roots here?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I posted my latest GameCube Moments video today, so I hope you&amp;#8217;ll check it out!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing - GameCube Moments #26" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vqV33NLvoBE?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Peak &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/guides/ac/september-fishing.htm"&gt;ocean fishing season&lt;/a&gt; is right around the corner! I may have to give it a try early this September, so it may not be long until the next entry lands. I hope to see you again soon, and good luck fishing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/08/31/farmers-letter/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-08-31T21:02:48-04:00"&gt;August 31, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ac-coco-out-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>High Maintenance Rosie - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 31 Aug 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13582" class="post-13582 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;High Maintenance Rosie&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;I attended the fireworks festival last Sunday night, and I used a Roman candle to light a fire under Tortimer&amp;#8217;s&amp;#8230;shell. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="Lighting up Tortimer's shell during the fireworks festival." class="wp-image-13585" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;This always used to be a tradition of mine, going back to the days of playing online with Kimmy/Megan. I think I may have missed a year or two since, but I did it this year at least. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I also accomplished something else I set out to do: I saved Biskit from moving. He agreed to stick around for a while longer. 🙂&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="Biskit: Hmm... Well, when you put it THAT way, I guess I don't really wanna leave after all!" class="wp-image-13586" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I gave Rosie some more medicine Sunday night. By Thursday, she was all better.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="Rosie: You were like one of those TV docs who runs around and yells stat! and screams and whatever!" class="wp-image-13587" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She rewarded me with an azalea bonsai, and she was excited to go skateboarding again. (Again?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Felicity was telling me about the town she came from. She said they used to come up parties to help them cool off in summer, like a &amp;#8220;mini fireworks fiesta.&amp;#8221; She said the kids got fireworks, and the grown-ups&amp;#8230;ate fish. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="Felicity: The kids got fireworks, and the grown-ups...um...ate fish. Ah, good times!" class="wp-image-13588" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I saw Big Top and Nana having an argument from across the river. By the time I got around there, the fight was over&amp;#8230;but Nana was still mad, and going bananas. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="Nana: Augh! I have nothing to say right now, banana man!" class="wp-image-13589" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Okay, Furious George.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I was looking through the fish and bug information, and I was slightly horrified when I read that goliath beetles can fly like birds. Yikes! The thought of huge beetles flapping around everywhere almost turns me into Blathers. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="Goliath beetle: The largest of its kind in the world, these can fly like birds." class="wp-image-13590" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I later went over to the Roost for K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s show. I asked for a random song, as usual. He performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Aria&amp;#8221; for me. It&amp;#8217;s a slow, sad song, but it&amp;#8217;s not bad.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Aria." class="wp-image-13591" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And of course now that Rosie is healthy and outside again, she drops another bomb on me: She&amp;#8217;s moving! Again! &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/Array" alt="Rosie: I'm moving, la-di-da!" class="wp-image-13592" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She&amp;#8217;s starting to feel very high maintenance lately. I asked her to stay, and she initially said she was still moving. But then she said if I keep asking her nicely, maybe she&amp;#8217;ll change her mind. However, I&amp;#8217;ve seen this dialogue before and I *&lt;em&gt;think&lt;/em&gt;* it actually means that she&amp;#8217;s staying. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I wonder if that line and the other line (from when she first told me she was safe last time) got switched, and assigned to the wrong outcomes. I don&amp;#8217;t know, but after battling to save Rosie twice, then Biskit, and now Rosie again, I&amp;#8217;m kinda drained by this constant back-and-forth stuff.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tomorrow is not only the final fireworks festival of the year, but also the final night of peak bug season! I plan on participating in both, and I&amp;#8217;ll tell Rosie to stick around if she asks again. But regardless, I&amp;#8217;ll be back early in the week with my summer wrap-up, discussing how my summer bug-hunting goals ended up. Hope to see you then!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/30/high-maintenance-rosie/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-30T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;August 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-31T01:30:14-04:00"&gt;August 31, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/RUU_8329-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Duck, No Cover - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 31 Aug 2025 03:01:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18339" class="post-18339 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Duck, No Cover&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Leonardo the lion was camping out at the campsite. He wanted to play a game with me, but it involved me buying something from him (potentially at a high price), so I declined the request.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Leonardo, at the campsite: Oh noooo! This is such a fun game to play..." class="wp-image-18340" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Molly asked me to play a game of hide-and-seek with her. She assured me that she was really good at hiding.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Molly: It might surprise you, but I'm quite good at hiding!" class="wp-image-18341" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She gave me 15 minutes to find her, Rolf, and Inkwell.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Molly: If you can find all of us within 15 minutes, you win!" class="wp-image-18342" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But within seconds, I had already found Molly! The starting banner hadn&amp;#8217;t even disappeared off-screen yet. And Molly was the one that was so sure she was good at hiding! I guess she &lt;em&gt;quacked &lt;/em&gt;under the pressure.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="I spotted Molly seconds after the game began." class="wp-image-18343" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;The duck forgot to cover.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Since I had a lot of time to search, I took my time and stopped to catch an eel over near Lolly&amp;#8217;s house. But I spotted something else in the background&amp;#8230;Inkwell!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="I caught an eel! Things just got REAL! 47.20 in." class="wp-image-18344" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Seconds later, I also caught a big orange squid.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And with 11 and a half minutes still on the timer, I found Rolf trying to hide behind the instrument shelter! That was still a quick win, even though I wasn&amp;#8217;t rushing. They were just really bad at hiding this time. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Rolf peeks out from behind the instrument shelter." class="wp-image-18345" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Molly gave me a kiwi stool as my prize for winning.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Molly: to thank you for playing with us, we're giving you a kiwi stool!" class="wp-image-18349" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Hornsby approached me and told me that he spent all of his money on a chocolate fountain. Easy to do. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Hornsby: So, uh, cupcake. I spent the last of my pocket money on a chocolate fountain." class="wp-image-18350" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He wanted me to buy it for 1,760 bells. I meant to say no, but I guess I clicked the wrong thing and ended up buying it anyway. Oh well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Hornsby sent me a racer 6 tee in the mail. I decided to put it on, just to wear something different.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Cube wanted me to visit his house, so we had to schedule a time (6 p.m.). I don&amp;#8217;t normally agree to these, but I make exceptions when I still need a villager&amp;#8217;s photo. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Cube: Yo, Mr. J! This is short notice, but wanna come see my place?" class="wp-image-18356" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Moments later, Cube asked for a new catchphrase. I told him to say &amp;#8220;it froze,&amp;#8221; although that choice hasn&amp;#8217;t paid off just yet.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I shook a nearby tree, and a bathtub fell out! Oops! I hope it didn&amp;#8217;t belong to Agent S or some other squirrel who lived up there. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Standing by a bathtub that fell out of a tree." class="wp-image-18351" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When 6:00 rolled around, I ran over to Cube&amp;#8217;s house.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Cube: Welcome to my home! I hope you like it as much as I do, it froze." class="wp-image-18352" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He didn&amp;#8217;t give me any gifts, but he did ask if I wanted to buy anything. I ultimately bought his astro CD player for 2,150 bells. After ten minutes of pointless, repetitious chat and standing around, I left.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This morning, Cube sent me a letter talking about my visit yesterday. He sent me a gift, but it was just an hourglass. Clearly he&amp;#8217;s mocking me for all the time (the years, really) that I&amp;#8217;ve been trying to earn his photo. 😛 ⏳&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jeremiah seemed like he wasn&amp;#8217;t fully awake yet. He said the sun was so bright that it felt like lasers were shooting into his brain. Maybe he had a late night of club-&lt;em&gt;hopping&lt;/em&gt;. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="Jeremiah: Plus, the sun is so bright, it feels like lasers are shooting directly into my brain, hip hop." class="wp-image-18354" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tonight, I made a rare trip up to Club LOL. K.K. Slider was around, so I asked him for a random song. He performed &amp;#8220;Only Me&amp;#8221; for me, Hamlet, and Hippeux. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/Array" alt="K.K. Slider performs for Hippeux, Jeff, and Hamlet, as the game credits roll." class="wp-image-18355" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;(Well actually, Dr. Shrunk was in the back shaking his booty too.) 😆&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/30/duck-no-cover/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-30T23:01:50-04:00"&gt;August 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-30T23:06:15-04:00"&gt;August 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/20250827_HNI_0049.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Pascal and Resetti - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 31 Aug 2025 01:39:26 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8950" class="post-8950 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Pascal and Resetti&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, Pascal popped up to ponder how hard it is to have an unbiased opinion of your own brain.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/Array" alt="Pascal: You ever thought about how hard it is to have an unbiased opinion about your own brain? Maaan, don't." class="wp-image-8951" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That is a good point, but &lt;em&gt;my &lt;/em&gt;brain is just surprised that I keep encountering new quotes from Pascal 5+ years into playing this game daily.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Somehow, I manged to catch three banded dragonflies in one day on Sunday. The thrill of seeing, and chasing down, banded dragonflies is probably the only thing in the newer games that approaches the excitement of seeing a UFO in City Folk and Wild World.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/Array" alt="Me, after catching my third banded dragonfly of the day: I did it!" class="wp-image-8952" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Monday, I ran into Pascal again while diving. He gave me another good quote that I haven&amp;#8217;t yet posted on the blog before.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/Array" alt="Pascal: Friendship isn't a boat you crew alone. You never know when you'll need all hands on deck for a storm." class="wp-image-8953" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;What if you only have a kayak?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I ran into Resetti at the Roost. He was declaring victory over reset buttons, since they&amp;#8217;re basically obsolete now. (I guess he doesn&amp;#8217;t know you can still reset, even if there isn&amp;#8217;t a designated reset button.)&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/Array" alt="Resetti: My old enemy, the reset button... Didja know they're basically obsolete? Ha! Looks like I won!" class="wp-image-8954" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Except for the fact that you&amp;#8217;re basically obsolete too. Yeah, I went there.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But then he got a bit more reflective, wondering if a reset button is actually a good thing! Wow, I never thought Resetti himself would say such a thing. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/Array" alt="Resetti: But now that I'm a little older, I get to thinkin'...what if reset buttons are actually...good?" class="wp-image-8955" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;OK, who are you, and what have you done with the real Resetti?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you haven&amp;#8217;t seen it yet, I recently posted an hour-long gameplay video of my bug and fish hunt from last week. Here it is:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing: New Horizons - Bug &amp;amp; Fish Hunt (1 hour of gameplay)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KTb85lo5HEQ?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And here are a few other quick notes about the past week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Monday, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;The K. Funk&amp;#8221; for me and Louie.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, I sold 26 fish to C.J. for 357,750 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I also separately sold my fish from last week&amp;#8217;s fish hunt, and my calculation given in the video was correct.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Condor&amp;#8221; for me and Ketchup. One of my favorites! &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/30/pascal-and-resetti/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-30T21:39:26-04:00"&gt;August 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-30T21:43:01-04:00"&gt;August 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/pascal-unbiased-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
